It's the same design as the Type 1 dual relief case.

>Sorry to sound silly, but am I correct in assuming "oil pressure relief" just
>bypasses the cooler, and the "oil control" bleeds excess oil to the sump? (I
>don't have my Bentley handy).

The pressure relief value bypasses the oil cooler but if the pressure is too much the oil goes into the sump like it does with the control valve.

